# Product Vision

## Purpose

{{ project_name }} exists to deliver a focused frontend experience for users who need a clear, reliable and fast interface.

## Product Intent

Describe the real user problem before describing features. A good product intent explains who the product serves, what outcome they need and why the current alternatives are insufficient.

## Primary Outcomes

- Users can understand the product state quickly.
- Users can complete the primary workflow without unnecessary navigation.
- The interface handles loading, empty and error states explicitly.
- The product can evolve through small vertical slices.

## Workflow

Use `docs/workflow.md` as the source of truth for the full product-to-implementation workflow.

At a high level, start with product intent, define the affected users and flows, specify screens and states, then plan implementation through small vertical tasks. Create PRDs for large product changes and record significant decisions as ADRs.

## Non-Goals

- Do not add generic dashboard features before a real workflow requires them.
- Do not build reusable components before at least one screen state proves the need.
- Do not introduce global state for local interactions.
